{
    "title": "Excel Functions and Charts: Party Planning",
    "steps": [
        {
            "title": "Basic Excel Functions",
            "content": "<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-4\">Essential Excel Functions</h2><div class=\"download-notice\">Download and use the Party planning file for these activities.</div><p class=\"mb-4 font-bold\">Create a new sheet named 'Functions Practice':</p><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cpWB3TB.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div><div class=\"bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6 mt-4\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Functions: Quick Recap</h3><p class=\"mb-4\">Excel functions start with an equals sign (<span class=\"key operator\">=</span>) followed by the function name and data range.</p><ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1\"><li class=\"mb-2\"><span class=\"term\" id=\"sum\">SUM</span>: Adds up numbers in a range</li><li class=\"mb-2\"><span class=\"term\" id=\"counta\">COUNTA</span>: Counts cells that aren't empty</li><li class=\"mb-2\"><span class=\"term\" id=\"max\">MAX</span>: Finds the highest number</li><li class=\"mb-2\"><span class=\"term\" id=\"min\">MIN</span>: Finds the lowest number</li></ul></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 1: Total Recipe Cost</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using the Party shopping list sheet, calculate the total cost of all items needed for the party. Copy your formula and result to your 'Functions Practice' sheet.</p><div class=\"view-solution\"><button class=\"solution-toggle\" onclick=\"toggleSolution(this)\">View Solution <i class=\"fas fa-chevron-down\"></i></button><div class=\"solution-content\"><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/D9VLCVu.png\" alt=\"SUM function example\" /></div><div class=\"formula mb-4\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>SUM(<span class=\"cell-ref\">F2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">F6</span>)</div></div></div></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 2: Recipe Analysis</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using Recipe ingredients, calculate the total quantities needed for each recipe (Choc-chip muffins, Blueberry muffins, Cupcakes). Copy your formulas and results to your 'Functions Practice' sheet.</p></div>",
            "quiz": [
                {
                    "question": "Using the Party shopping list sheet, how would you calculate the total cost of all items?",
                    "options": ["<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNT(<span class=\"cell-ref\">F</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">F</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>SUM(<span class=\"cell-ref\">F2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">F6</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>TOTAL(<span class=\"cell-ref\">F</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">F</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>ADD(<span class=\"cell-ref\">F2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">F6</span>)</div>"],
                    "correctAnswer": 1
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Using COUNTA for Ingredients",
            "content": "<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-4\">Tracking Ingredients</h2><p class=\"mb-4 font-bold\">Create a new sheet named 'Ingredient Count':</p><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cpWB3TB.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 1: Count Ingredients</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using Inside one cake, count how many unique ingredients we need. Copy your formula and result to your 'Ingredient Count' sheet.</p><div class=\"view-solution\"><button class=\"solution-toggle\" onclick=\"toggleSolution(this)\">View Solution <i class=\"fas fa-chevron-down\"></i></button><div class=\"solution-content\"><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/QcmHGY2.png\" alt=\"COUNTA function example\" /></div><div class=\"formula mb-2\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNTA(<span class=\"cell-ref\">A2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">A68</span>)<span class=\"key operator\">-</span>7</div><p class=\"mb-4\">We minus 7 because we don't want to include the actual recipe names among the ingredients.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 2: Measurement Types</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Count how many different measurement types (Measured in column) are used. Copy your formula and result to your 'Ingredient Count' sheet.</p></div>",
            "quiz": [
                {
                    "question": "To count the number of ingredients for Blueberry Muffins in Inside one cake, which formula would you use?",
                    "options": [
                        "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>SUM(<span class=\"cell-ref\">A13</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">A19</span>)</div>",
                        "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNTA(<span class=\"cell-ref\">A13</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">A19</span>)</div>",
                        "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNT(<span class=\"cell-ref\">A13</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">A19</span>)</div>",
                        "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>TOTAL(<span class=\"cell-ref\">A13</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">A19</span>)</div>"
                    ],
                    "correctAnswer": 1
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Using MAX and MIN Functions",
            "content": "<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-4\">Finding Cost Ranges</h2><p class=\"mb-4 font-bold\">Create a new sheet named 'Cost Analysis':</p><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cpWB3TB.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6 mt-4\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 1: Item Cost Range</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using the Party shopping list sheet, find the most and least expensive items (Price for one pack column). Copy your formulas and results to your 'Cost Analysis' sheet.</p><div class=\"view-solution\"><button class=\"solution-toggle\" onclick=\"toggleSolution(this)\">View Solution <i class=\"fas fa-chevron-down\"></i></button><div class=\"solution-content\"><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ohjagJ6.png\" alt=\"MAX and MIN function example\" /></div><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/O0dYY2y.png\" alt=\"MAX and MIN function example\" /></div><div class=\"formula mb-2\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>MAX(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C6</span>)</div><div class=\"formula mb-2\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>MIN(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C6</span>)</div></div></div></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 2: Servings Analysis</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Find the highest and lowest number of servings per pack. Copy your formulas and results to your 'Cost Analysis' sheet.</p></div>",
            "quiz": [
                {
                    "question": "Which function would you use to find the most expensive item in the Price for one pack column?",
                    "options": ["<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>SUM(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNTA(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>MAX(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C956</span>)</div>", "<div class=\"formula\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>LARGEST(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C</span>)</div>"],
                    "correctAnswer": 2
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Creating Visual Reports",
            "content": "<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-4\">Visualizing Recipe Data</h2><p class=\"mb-4 font-bold\">Create a new sheet named 'Charts Practice':</p><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cpWB3TB.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 1: Recipe Ingredients Chart</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using Recipe ingredients, create a bar chart comparing the number of ingredients needed for each recipe. Copy your chart to your 'Charts Practice' sheet.</p><div class=\"view-solution\"><button class=\"solution-toggle\" onclick=\"toggleSolution(this)\">View Solution <i class=\"fas fa-chevron-down\"></i></button><div class=\"solution-content\"><ol class=\"list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-2\"><li>Use COUNTA to count the number of ingredients needed (e.g. <span class=\"formula-inline\"><span class=\"key operator\">=</span>COUNTA(<span class=\"cell-ref\">C2</span>:<span class=\"cell-ref\">C22</span>)</span> gives 8 ingredients for choc-chip muffins). Use autofill to do the other columns automatically.</li><li>Copy and paste the header columns above the count values.</li></ol><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Dbaw37M.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of columns with headers\" /></div><ol class=\"list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-2\" start=\"3\"><li>Select the data (including the headers!) and go insert → recommended chart.</li></ol><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/jz7lNDC.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div></div></div></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 2: Cost Distribution</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Using the Party shopping list sheet, create a pie chart showing the cost distribution of different items. Copy your chart to your 'Charts Practice' sheet.</p></div><div class=\"bg-blue-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-8\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-black\">Submit Your Work</h3><p class=\"text-black\">Once you've completed all exercises, your Excel file should contain these sheets:</p><ul class=\"list-disc list-inside text-black space-y-1\"><li>Functions Practice</li><li>Ingredient Count</li><li>Cost Analysis</li><li>Charts Practice</li></ul><p class=\"text-black mt-4\">Save your file and submit it to the Party Planning link under Course Outline.</p></div>",
            "quiz": [
                {
                    "question": "Which chart type would be best for comparing ingredient quantities across recipes?",
                    "options": ["Pie Chart", "Bar Chart", "Line Chart", "Scatter Plot"],
                    "correctAnswer": 1
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
